The question tin-n arises: Why was this attempt made to prove Archias an alien, after twenty-seven ,νοω-δ’ unchallenged enjoyment of the Roman franchise 1> 'she nnswer is to be found in the political situation of those eventful years. The old rivali-y between Pompeius and Lucullus· came to a head when the former was appointed to take over the command against Mithri- dates. Not only was Pompeius empowered by the Lex Manilia to debar Lucullus srom completing his work, but his adherents busied themselves, during his absence at the seat of war, in intrigues to rob the deposed general of a richly-deserved triumph. It was not celebrated by Lucullus until the beginning of the year 63. His vindictive opponents then instituted this vexatious suit against Archias; with the sole object, apparently, of humiliating Lucullus by the expulsion from Rome of an old friend and professed eulogist. That they were foiled in this attempt seems certain.
